field.value:
The current behaviour for generation dictionary keys using the prefix attribute is, in my opinion, flawed. A prefix at any level of inheritence between interfaces "overrides" any other prefixes set up at alternative levels in the interface hierarchy. This is causing problems for me at the moment where I am using the prefixes to act as namespaces for my session variables. This patch changes the behaviour:

interface A { Prop1 { get; set; }}

interface B { Prop2 { get; set; }}

[DictionaryAdapterKeyPrefix("C")]
interface C { Prop3 { get; set; }}

[DictionaryAdapterKeyPrefix("D")]
interface D { Prop4 { get; set; }}

interface E { Prop5 { get; set; }}

Keys generated:

Prop1
Prop2
C.Prop3
D.Prop4
D.Prop5
